
/*
 * This example demonstrates how to convert an image file from PNG to WEBP format using the [image.convert] slot.
 *
 * 1. [image.convert]
 *    * Invokes the image conversion process.
 *
 * 2. [file:/input.png]
 *    * Specifies the source image file to convert, in this case 'input.png'.
 *
 * 3. [output:/output.webp]
 *    * Specifies the target image path and format, here being a WEBP file named 'output.webp'.
 *
 * Use case:
 * * Useful when you want to optimize images for web delivery by converting them into a more compressed format like WebP.
 */
image.convert
   file:/input.png
   output:/output.webp
